IAM - Identity and Access Management
AWS IAM is a service that helps securly control access to AWS resources

IAM Components - Users, Groups, Roles, Policies, Access advisor, Credential report, Access Analyzer, Organization

Types of users : 1) Root User - The root user is created when the account is created    2) IAM User - IAM users are created by root user or an IAM administrator for the account

Managed policies :
1)AWS managed policies - created and managed by AWS
2)Customer managed policies - created and managed by AWS account owner

IAM user - An AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM) user is an entity that you create in AWS to represent the person that uses it to interact with AWS.
